{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 43, "line_start": 43, "page_hint": null, "section": "Oak Ridge, Tennessee", "text": "Contract No W-7405-eng-26"}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 266, "line_start": 266, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "The build-up of uranium isotopes with time in a $U^{233}$ breeder core was calculated for five different cases, the difference depending on the starting fuel and the isotopic composition of the continuously added make-up fuel."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 266, "line_start": 266, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "The total uranium concentration was found to approach slowly an equilibrium value of 2.6 to 3.5 times the starting value, depending on the composition of the make-up fuel."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 266, "line_start": 266, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "In all cases the net neutron losses per net neutron reproduced in the core go through a maximum of less than $1\\%$ at a flux-time of about $3 \\times 10^{21}$ , go through a minimum of about $-0.6\\%$ (i.e. a net gain) at about a flux-time of $4 \\times 10^{22}$ , and approach equilibrium values of about $0.3\\%$ at flux-times above $6 \\times 10^{23}$ ."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 268, "line_start": 268, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "The principle heavy isotopes in the core of a $\\mathbf{U}^{233}$ breeder reactor and their modes of formation may be depicted by the following diagram."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 274, "line_start": 274, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "The production of these species as well as of several other heavy nuclides in the core of a breeder starting with pure $\\mathbf{U}^{233}$ has been discussed by Visner(1)"}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 280, "line_start": 280, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "Stoughton, ORNL-1368 (Sept."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 292, "line_start": 292, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "Pure $U^{235}$ in core at start, $U^{233}$ containing $5\\%$ $U^{234}$ added to core."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 296, "line_start": 296, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "chain (Th $^{233}$ , Pa $^{233}$ and U $^{233}$ ) and it is felt that an upper limit on the U $^{234}$ /U $^{233}$ ratio for the blanket product will be about 0.05 if the overall losses are to be kept within reason."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 296, "line_start": 296, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "Hence any practical case is expected to lie somewhere in between Cases IV and V - Cases I, II and III are included for comparison and because some future reactors may actually start with U $^{233}$ in the core - The effect of U $^{237}$ will not be considered because it is expected to be destroyed predominantly by beta decay and its cross-sections are not known."}
{"claim_type": "measurement", "line_end": 296, "line_start": 296, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "Its concentrations and possible effects have been considered in a previous paper(1)"}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 298, "line_start": 298, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "For Case I the concentration of $U^{233}$ is considered constant."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 298, "line_start": 298, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "Actually its concentration will increase somewhat as various pile poisons (e.g. fission products, $U^{234}$ etc.) grow in and its concentration may then decrease somewhat in the core as it increases in the blanket."}
{"claim_type": "technical-statement", "line_end": 298, "line_start": 298, "page_hint": null, "section": "Abstract", "text": "The effect of the heavy isotope build-up itself on required $U^{233}$ concentration changes is small as will be seen from the small effect of this build-up on neutron economy."}
